%h1.margin_bottom_20 Markdown Syntax

.inset

  %p
    Open Hub supports rich syntax in its forums. The syntax we use is called 'Markdown'. There are several libraries that support this syntax. We happen to use <a href='http://www.openhub.net/projects/3741'>BlueCloth</a>. Here's a reference:

  %h4 Phrase Emphasis
  %code
    *italic*   **bold**
    %br
    _italic_   __bold__
  %hr.one

.inset
  %h4 Links
  %h6.soft Inline
  %code
    An [example](http://url.com/ "Title")
  %br
  %br
  %h6.soft Reference-style labels (titles are optional)
  %code
    An [example][id]. Then, anywhere
    %br
    else in the doc, define the link:
    %br
    [id]: http://example.com/  "Title"
  %hr.one

.inset
  %h4 Images
  %h6.soft Inline (titles are optional)
  %code ![alt text](/path/img.jpg "Title")
  %hr.one
  %h6.soft Reference-style
  %code
    ![alt text][id]
    %br
    [id]: /url/to/img.jpg "Title"
  %hr.one

.inset
  %h4 Headers
  %h6.soft Setext-style
  %code
    Header 1
    %br
    \========
    %br
    Header 2
    %br
    \--------
  %hr.one
  %h6.soft atx-style (closing #'s are optional)
  %code
    \# Header 1 #
    %br
    \## Header 2 ##
    %br
    \###### Header 6
  %hr.one

.inset
  %h4 Lists
  %h6.soft Ordered, without paragraphs
  %code
    1.  Foo
    %br
    2.  Bar
  %hr.one
  %h6.soft Unordered
  %code
    \*   A list item.
    %br
    \*   Bar
  %hr.one
  %h6.soft You can nest them
  %code
    \* Abacus
    %br
    &nbsp; &nbsp; * answer
    %br
    \* Bubbles
    %br
    &nbsp; &nbsp; 1. bunk
    %br
    &nbsp; &nbsp; 2. bupkis
    %br
    &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; * BELITTLER
    %br
    &nbsp; &nbsp; 3. burper
    %br
    \*   Cunning
  %hr.one

.inset
  %h4 Blockquotes
  %code
    &gt; Email-style angle brackets
    %br
    &gt; are used for blockquotes.
    %br
    &gt; &gt; And, they can be nested.
    %br
    &gt; #### Headers in blockquotes
    %br
    &gt; 
    %br
    &gt; * You can quote a list.
    %br
    &gt; * Etc.
    %br
  %hr.one

.inset
  %h4 Code Spans
  %code
    `&lt;code&gt;` spans are delimited by backticks.
    %br
    You can include literal backticks like `` `this` ``.
  %hr.one

.inset
  %h4 Preformatted Code Blocks
  %p Indent every line of a code block by at least 4 spaces or 1 tab.
  %code
    This is a normal paragraph.
    %br
    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; This is a preformatted
    %br
    &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; code block.
  %hr.one

.inset
  %h4 Horizontal Rules
  %p Three or more dashes or asterisks
  %code
    \---
    %br
    \* * *
    %br
    \- - - -
  %hr.one

.inset
  %h4 Manual Line Breaks
  %p End a line with two or more spaces:
  %code
    Roses are red,&lt;space&gt;&lt;space&gt;
    %br   
    Violets are blue.